<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>ViT on Svtter's Blog</title><link>https://svtter.cn/tags/vit/</link><description>Recent content in ViT on Svtter's Blog</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>zh-cn</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 19 Mar 2025 13:23:50 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://svtter.cn/tags/vit/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Read Code of CLIP.md</title><link>https://svtter.cn/p/read-code-of-clip.md/</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Mar 2025 13:23:50 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://svtter.cn/p/read-code-of-clip.md/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://svtter.cn/p/read-code-of-clip.md/image.png" alt="Featured image of post Read Code of CLIP.md" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Contrastive Language-Image Pre-Training (CLIP) 是 openai 的经典工作之一。出自论文&lt;a class="link" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2103.00020" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
